Dresden Files - Your Story&lt;/cite&gt;, &lt;cite&gt;The Dresden Files - Our World&lt;/cite&gt;, and a
gift copy of &lt;cite&gt;Hero System Sidekick&lt;/cite&gt; &lt;a class="footnote-reference brackets" href="https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2011/05/26/recent-rpg-arrivals/#sidekick" id="id1"&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;cite&gt;Your Story&lt;/cite&gt; and &lt;cite&gt;Our World&lt;/cite&gt; look very impressive after a first quick
scan.  I like all the annotations and marginal notes, although I'd
have preferred that the post-it notes had been marginal notes as well.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;dl class="footnote brackets"&gt;
&lt;dt class="label" id="sidekick"&gt;&lt;span class="brackets"&gt;&lt;a class="fn-backref" href="https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2011/05/26/recent-rpg-arrivals/#id1"&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;
&lt;dd&gt;&lt;p&gt;That makes my second gift copy of &lt;cite&gt;Sidekick&lt;/cite&gt;, and three copies
in total.  I'm sure that means I'm destined to run a &lt;cite&gt;Sidekick&lt;/cite&gt;
campaign for the kids, when they're all old enough for Hero 5ER
&lt;a class="footnote-reference brackets" href="https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2011/05/26/recent-rpg-arrivals/#er" id="id2"&gt;2&lt;/a&gt; math.  And I am &lt;a class="footnote-reference brackets" href="https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2011/05/26/recent-rpg-arrivals/#ermath" id="id3"&gt;3&lt;/a&gt;. :-)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/dd&gt;
&lt;dt class="label" id="er"&gt;&lt;span class="brackets"&gt;&lt;a class="fn-backref" href="https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2011/05/26/recent-rpg-arrivals/#id2"&gt;2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;
&lt;dd&gt;&lt;p&gt;That's &lt;cite&gt;Hero System&lt;/cite&gt;, Fifth Edition, Revised.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/dd&gt;
&lt;dt class="label" id="ermath"&gt;&lt;span class="brackets"&gt;&lt;a class="fn-backref" href="https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2011/05/26/recent-rpg-arrivals/#id3"&gt;3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;
&lt;dd&gt;&lt;p&gt;Actually, the kids are probably readier for that than I
am.  I'm liking less and less math at the game table as I grow
older and have less time to prepare and play.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/dd&gt;
&lt;/dl&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>dresden files</category><category>houses of the blooded</category><category>rpg</category><guid>https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2011/05/26/recent-rpg-arrivals/</guid><pubDate>Fri, 27 May 2011 01:25:40 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>